# Continue Build With Test Safety

- Continue building the project plan until the build-out is complete when the user has authorized ongoing work.
- Keep work in small, tested slices and update the project plan as the implementation state changes.
- As long as tests pass, continue to the next relevant build slice without requiring the user to confirm each step.
- Do not delete, remove, skip, xfail, or ignore a valid failing test just to make the suite pass.
- If a relevant test fails, fix the implementation or test fixture honestly, then rerun the affected tests and the full suite before committing.
- Push completed passing slices to the active development branch when the user has authorized GitHub updates.
